sec.p: Modelling procedure generated a subset of 37 models to explain fledging rate ( Table 4). Due to their small differences in AICc values, our results did not lend definitive support to any of them. Nevertheless, the variable year was present in all the models (Σωi = 1.00), as fledging rate was higher in 2013 ( Fig. S3, Supporting Information). Influential were also HA (Σωi = 0.88) and RWD (Σωi = 0.62) as both of them negatively affected fledging rate ( Fig. 5a,b). Finally, species was influential as well (Σωi = 0.70), having blue tits larger fledging rates than great tits ( Fig. 5c).
